&lt;p&gt;MerQube is a cutting-edge fintech firm, specializing in the development of advanced technology for indexing and rules-based investing. We offer innovative solutions for designing and calculating complex, rules-based strategies. Founded in 2019 by a team of index industry veterans and technology experts, MerQube provides a tech-focused alternative in the indexing space, with offices in New York, London, Bangalore and Vina Del Mar.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MerQube designs and calculates a wide variety of indices, including thematic, ESG, QIS, and delta one strategies, spanning multiple asset classes such as equities, futures, and options. Leveraging cloud-based architecture and advanced index-tracking technology, our platform enables clients to bring new ideas to market swiftly and efficiently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Platform Support Engineer to help maintain and improve the reliability of MerQube’s production systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will investigate technical issues, debug backend services and data pipelines, and work closely with engineers across the organization to diagnose and resolve system problems. You will gain deep visibility into MerQube’s platform and play an important role in ensuring that our systems operate reliably for internal teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is ideal for engineers who enjoy problem solving, debugging complex systems, and learning how large-scale platforms operate. Support Engineers work across multiple parts of the system, making this role a great opportunity to develop a broad understanding of backend architecture, data pipelines, and financial data processing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also help identify recurring issues and collaborate with the broader engineering team to improve system reliability and reduce operational friction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will you do?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate and diagnose &lt;strong&gt;production issues, bugs, and system failures&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with internal engineering teams to &lt;strong&gt;resolve technical issues impacting the platform&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Debug &lt;strong&gt;backend services, APIs, and distributed systems&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot issues in &lt;strong&gt;data ingestion pipelines, ETL workflows, and computation processes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform &lt;strong&gt;root cause analysis (RCA)&lt;/strong&gt; on production incidents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify recurring operational issues and propose improvements to increase system reliability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with engineers to implement fixes and improve system stability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use logs, monitoring tools, and debugging techniques to analyze system behavior&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document troubleshooting processes and common operational workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a broad understanding of MerQube’s systems and financial data infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;On-Call Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role includes participation in a &lt;strong&gt;light on-call rotation&lt;/strong&gt; focused on responding to critical production incidents.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most work occurs during &lt;strong&gt;regular business hours&lt;/strong&gt; supporting internal teams. During on-call periods, engineers ensure that &lt;strong&gt;high-priority incidents (P1 issues)&lt;/strong&gt; are addressed in a timely manner by either resolving the issue directly or coordinating with the appropriate engineering teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The on-call rotation is designed to provide coverage for critical incidents and is &lt;strong&gt;not intended to require continuous off-hours work&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
